        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 3:54PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 354 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Locker, or near Skeeterville, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
San Saba, Richland Springs, Algerita, Sloan, Skeeterville,
Harkeyville, Locker, and Spring Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
